    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-24T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-24T05:00:00-05:00" n="925"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d925">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.24/150: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-24T13:00:00+03:00"
                            >May 24, 1941—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 24—11:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>168. In view of the frequent complaints of the local press previously reported
                    (although not shared in informed official circles) as to our alleged slowness in
                    furnishing aid to Turkey and other small countries and of my lack of any
                    definite information on the subject, I should appreciate being informed more
                    specifically as to the nature and extent of the aid mentioned in your telegram
                    No. 72, May 17, 4 p.m.,<note n="55" xml:id="d925fn55">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_936">p. 936</ref>.</note> as
                    having been already extended to Turkey under the Lease-Lend Act and as to any
                    arrangements for such aid in future.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
